  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (synthetic adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed across 5 flow-speed operating combinations. All 13 credibility factors are assessed; achieved levels meet or exceed required levels at the Low assurance tier. Hemolysis index predictions remain below the absolute clinical threshold across all operating points. Decision: Accepted. Supporting methodology follows the power-law hemolysis damage accumulation approach documented in the literature (see referencesIdentifier).",
